 "Riddles": [
   "As I walked, I saw something with four fingers and one thumb. It was not flesh, fish, bone, or fowl.",
   "Barrel of water weighs 20 pounds. What must you add to it to make it weigh 12 pounds?",
   "Give it food and it will live; give it water and it will die.",
   "He has married many women but has never married. Who is he?",
   "I have holes on the top and bottom. I have holes on my left and my right. ",
   "And I have holes in the middle, yet I still hold water. What am I?",
   "I look at you, you look at me, I raise my right, you raise your left. What is this object?",
   "I run, yet I have no legs. What am I?",
   "I went into the woods and got it, I sat down to seek it, I brought it home because I could not find it.",
   "If you have it, you want to share it. If you share it, you don’t have it. What is it?",
   "It has no top or bottom but it can hold flesh, bones, and blood all at the same time. What is it?",
   "It is weightless, you can see it, and if you put it in a barrel it will make the barrel lighter?",
   "It’s been around for millions of years, but it’s no more than a month old. What is it?",
   "Light as a feather, there is nothing in it; the strongest man can’t hold it for much more than a minute.",
   "No sooner spoken than broken. What is it?",
   "Remove the outside, cook the inside, eat the outside, throw away the inside.",
   "Take off my skin, I won’t cry, but you will. What am I?",
   "Take one out and scratch my head, I am now black but once was red.",
   "The more there is, the less you see.",
   "The more you take the more you leave behind.",
   "They come at night without being called and are lost in the day without being stolen.",
   "What belongs to you but others use it more than you do?",
   "What can fill a room but takes up no space?",
   "What can go up and come down without moving?",
   "What can run but never walks, has a mouth but never talks, has a head but never weeps, has a bed but never sleeps?",
   "What comes once in a minute, twice in a moment, but never in a thousand years?",
   "What do you fill with empty hands?",
   "What do you throw out when you want to use it but take in when you don’t want to use it?",
   "What gets wetter the more it dries?",
   "What goes up and down stairs without moving?",
   "What goes up and never comes down?",
   "What has a foot on each side and one in the middle?",
   "What has to be broken before it can be used?",
   "What is it the more you take away the larger it becomes?",
   "What kind of coat can be put on only when wet?",
   "What kind of room has no windows or doors?",
   "What question can you never answer “yes” to?",
   "When one does not know it, then it is something; but when one knows what it is, then it is nothing.",
   "Who spends the day at the window, goes to the table for meals and hides at night?",
   "You answer me, although I never ask you questions. What am I?",
   "You can’t keep this until you have given it."
  ],
